problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone in preschool would. Let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
ax+3 & \text{ if }x>0, \\
ab & \text{ if }x=0, \\
bx+c & \text{ if }x<0.
\end{array}
\right.\]If $f(2)=5$, $f(0)=5$, and $f(-2)=-10$, and $a$, $b$, and $c$ are nonnegative integers, then what is $a+b+c$?
